## What is TPS?

**TPS = Transactions Per Second**

In the context of your Gatling test and application:

```
TPS ≈ RPS (Requests Per Second) for HTTP APIs
    = how many new requests arrive at your app every second
```

So when you set:

```bash
-DTPS="25"
```

You're saying: *"Ramp up to 25 new ACH requests arriving per second at peak."*

### TPS vs RPS vs Concurrent Users — Common Confusion

| Term | Meaning | Your Gatling Parameter |
|---|---|---|
| **TPS** | Transactions/sec — requests arriving | `-DTPS="25"` (ramp target) |
| **RPS** | Requests/sec — same thing for HTTP | same as TPS here |
| **Concurrent Users** | Users active simultaneously | `atOnceUsers(40)` |
| **CONSTANTUSERPERSEC** | Users injected each second | `-DCONSTANTUSERPERSEC="10"` |

### They relate like this:

```
Concurrent Users ≈ TPS × Avg Response Time (seconds)

Example:
TPS = 25 requests/sec
Avg response time = 3 seconds

Concurrent Users = 25 × 3 = 75 users active at any moment
```

